sql:
SELECT project_id, project_name, start_date, end_date, status
FROM code_projects
WHERE status = 'In Progress';

external_knowledge:
- Code coverage > 80% implies a high level of testing;
- Cyclomatic complexity < 10 suggests the code is not overly complex;
- Difficulty < 0.5 indicates that the code is relatively easy to understand based on Halstead's difficulty metric;
- Lines of code > 100 means the file contains more than 100 lines of actual code, excluding comments.

sql:
SELECT developers.developer_name, code_issues.issue_type, code_issues.issue_status, code_issues.priority
FROM developers
INNER JOIN code_issues ON developers.developer_id = code_issues.developer_id;

SELECT project_name, start_date, description
FROM code_projects
ORDER BY project_id;
